<subSubSection id="EBBF6528FF969E630BEEFC7B9FC3035C" pageId="5" pageNumber="254" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="A31A36A3FF969E630BEEFC7B9FC3035C" blockId="5.[151,1437,906,2013]" pageId="5" pageNumber="254">
<emphasis id="91D1EAB1FF969E630BEEFC7B9A2804A0" bold="true" box="[151,364,906,933]" pageId="5" pageNumber="254">Diagnosis. Larva.</emphasis>
1) labrum rectangular, broader than long, medially with two protuberances (
<figureCitation id="3B9E2A26FF969E630F93FC7A9E0304A0" box="[1258,1351,907,933]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[176,1408,182,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-30@6.[176,1411,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3A–J. Apobaetis jacobusi sp. nov. A. labrum (left d.v., right v.v.); B. left mandible; C. right mandible; D. maxilla; E. hypopharynx; F. labium (left d.v., right v.v.); G. foreleg; H. posterior margin of tergum IV; I. gill VI; J. paraproct." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4296592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4296592/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="254">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
); distal margin, between medial lobe and lateral denticle, with thin setae; 2) maxillary palp long, more than 2.0× the length of galea-lacinia; segment I robust, longer than galea-lacinia (
<figureCitation id="3B9E2A26FF969E630847FC2298DC04E8" box="[830,920,979,1005]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[176,1408,182,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-30@6.[176,1411,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3A–J. Apobaetis jacobusi sp. nov. A. labrum (left d.v., right v.v.); B. left mandible; C. right mandible; D. maxilla; E. hypopharynx; F. labium (left d.v., right v.v.); G. foreleg; H. posterior margin of tergum IV; I. gill VI; J. paraproct." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4296592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4296592/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="254">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
); 3) lingua subquadrate with one small medial lobe (
<figureCitation id="3B9E2A26FF969E630BAFFC069A680314" box="[214,300,1015,1041]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[176,1408,182,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-30@6.[176,1411,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3A–J. Apobaetis jacobusi sp. nov. A. labrum (left d.v., right v.v.); B. left mandible; C. right mandible; D. maxilla; E. hypopharynx; F. labium (left d.v., right v.v.); G. foreleg; H. posterior margin of tergum IV; I. gill VI; J. paraproct." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4296592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4296592/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="254">Fig. 3E</figureCitation>
); 4) glossa distally pointed (
<figureCitation id="3B9E2A26FF969E63091CFC0699FE0314" box="[613,698,1015,1041]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[176,1408,182,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-30@6.[176,1411,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3A–J. Apobaetis jacobusi sp. nov. A. labrum (left d.v., right v.v.); B. left mandible; C. right mandible; D. maxilla; E. hypopharynx; F. labium (left d.v., right v.v.); G. foreleg; H. posterior margin of tergum IV; I. gill VI; J. paraproct." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4296592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4296592/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="254">Fig. 3F</figureCitation>
); 5) inner projection of labial palp of segment II rounded, segment III of labial palp triangular (
<figureCitation id="3B9E2A26FF969E630AAAFBEA996D0330" box="[467,553,1051,1077]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[176,1408,182,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-30@6.[176,1411,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3A–J. Apobaetis jacobusi sp. nov. A. labrum (left d.v., right v.v.); B. left mandible; C. right mandible; D. maxilla; E. hypopharynx; F. labium (left d.v., right v.v.); G. foreleg; H. posterior margin of tergum IV; I. gill VI; J. paraproct." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4296592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4296592/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="254">Fig. 3F</figureCitation>
); 6) tarsal claw I with the same length as tarsus, without row of denticles (
<figureCitation id="3B9E2A26FF969E630E16FBEA9BF9035C" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[176,1408,182,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-30@6.[176,1411,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3A–J. Apobaetis jacobusi sp. nov. A. labrum (left d.v., right v.v.); B. left mandible; C. right mandible; D. maxilla; E. hypopharynx; F. labium (left d.v., right v.v.); G. foreleg; H. posterior margin of tergum IV; I. gill VI; J. paraproct." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4296592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4296592/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="254">Fig. 3G</figureCitation>
); 7) posterior margin of tergum IV with triangular spines (longer than wide) (
<figureCitation id="3B9E2A26FF969E630F59FBCE9F3E035C" box="[1056,1146,1087,1113]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[176,1408,182,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-30@6.[176,1411,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3A–J. Apobaetis jacobusi sp. nov. A. labrum (left d.v., right v.v.); B. left mandible; C. right mandible; D. maxilla; E. hypopharynx; F. labium (left d.v., right v.v.); G. foreleg; H. posterior margin of tergum IV; I. gill VI; J. paraproct." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4296592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4296592/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="254">Fig. 3H</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EBBF6528FF969E6E0BBEFB939FA50644" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="257" pageId="5" pageNumber="254" type="description">
<paragraph id="A31A36A3FF969E6E0BBEFB939FA50644" blockId="5.[151,1437,906,2013]" lastBlockId="8.[151,1437,151,645]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="257" pageId="5" pageNumber="254">
<emphasis id="91D1EAB1FF969E630BBEFB939AF40378" bold="true" box="[199,432,1122,1149]" pageId="5" pageNumber="254">Description. Larva.</emphasis>
Head: Antenna with minute spines and thin, simple setae on apex of each segment. Frons with two small parallel keels, slightly concave (almost flat) between keels. Labrum (
<figureCitation id="3B9E2A26FF969E630F35FB769FEC03A4" box="[1100,1192,1159,1185]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[176,1408,182,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-30@6.[176,1411,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3A–J. Apobaetis jacobusi sp. nov. A. labrum (left d.v., right v.v.); B. left mandible; C. right mandible; D. maxilla; E. hypopharynx; F. labium (left d.v., right v.v.); G. foreleg; H. posterior margin of tergum IV; I. gill VI; J. paraproct." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4296592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4296592/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="254">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
): rectangular, broader than long; distal margin without shallow medial emargination; medially with two protuberances, area between them with thin setae; medial area of distal margin with one row of long thin setae on dorsal surface; ventral surface with one row of robust setae at distal margin. Left mandible (
<figureCitation id="3B9E2A26FF969E630829FB0298EE0208" box="[848,938,1267,1293]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[176,1408,182,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-30@6.[176,1411,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3A–J. Apobaetis jacobusi sp. nov. A. labrum (left d.v., right v.v.); B. left mandible; C. right mandible; D. maxilla; E. hypopharynx; F. labium (left d.v., right v.v.); G. foreleg; H. posterior margin of tergum IV; I. gill VI; J. paraproct." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4296592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4296592/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="254">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
): outer and inner sets of incisors with 4 and 3 denticles, respectively; prostheca robust, inner margin frayed at distal half; margin between prostheca and mola concave, with frayed lobe close to subtriangular process; tuft of robust setae at base of mola present; subtriangular process wide; denticles of mola not constricted; lateral margin convex. Right mandible (
<figureCitation id="3B9E2A26FF969E630FF8FAAE9F9F027C" box="[1153,1243,1375,1401]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[176,1408,182,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-30@6.[176,1411,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3A–J. Apobaetis jacobusi sp. nov. A. labrum (left d.v., right v.v.); B. left mandible; C. right mandible; D. maxilla; E. hypopharynx; F. labium (left d.v., right v.v.); G. foreleg; H. posterior margin of tergum IV; I. gill VI; J. paraproct." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4296592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4296592/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="254">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
): outer and inner sets of incisors with 3 and 2 denticles, respectively; prostheca slender; margin between prostheca and mola concave; tuft of robust setae at base of mola present; denticles of mola not constricted; lateral margin convex. Maxilla (
<figureCitation id="3B9E2A26FF969E630E16FA569BF902E0" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[176,1408,182,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-30@6.[176,1411,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3A–J. Apobaetis jacobusi sp. nov. A. labrum (left d.v., right v.v.); B. left mandible; C. right mandible; D. maxilla; E. hypopharynx; F. labium (left d.v., right v.v.); G. foreleg; H. posterior margin of tergum IV; I. gill VI; J. paraproct." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4296592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4296592/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="254">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
): maxillary palp long, more than 2.0× the length of galea-lacinia; segment I robust, longer than galea-lacinia; segment II robust, without distal constriction; maxillary palp with thin, simple setae scattered over the surface. Hypopharynx (
<figureCitation id="3B9E2A26FF969E630A3BF9E29ADE0128" box="[322,410,1555,1581]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[176,1408,182,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-30@6.[176,1411,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3A–J. Apobaetis jacobusi sp. nov. A. labrum (left d.v., right v.v.); B. left mandible; C. right mandible; D. maxilla; E. hypopharynx; F. labium (left d.v., right v.v.); G. foreleg; H. posterior margin of tergum IV; I. gill VI; J. paraproct." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4296592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4296592/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="254">Fig. 3E</figureCitation>
): lingua subquadrate and longer than superlingua, with one small medial lobe and without distal tuft of setae; superlingua not expanded, with short, thin, simple setae scattered over distal margin. Labium (
<figureCitation id="3B9E2A26FF969E630BD9F9AA9BB10170" box="[160,245,1627,1653]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[176,1408,182,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-30@6.[176,1411,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3A–J. Apobaetis jacobusi sp. nov. A. labrum (left d.v., right v.v.); B. left mandible; C. right mandible; D. maxilla; E. hypopharynx; F. labium (left d.v., right v.v.); G. foreleg; H. posterior margin of tergum IV; I. gill VI; J. paraproct." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4296592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4296592/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="254">Fig. 3F</figureCitation>
): glossa narrowing slightly distally on inner margin and with apex pointed, longer than paraglossa; dorsal surface with one arc of robust setae on distal third, from inner to outer margin; ventral surface with distal row of robust setae, covered with thin setae. Paraglossa curved inward; dorsal surface with one longitudinal row of four robust setae near inner margin; apex with one robust seta; outer margin with one row of eight robust setae; ventral surface with one longitudinal row of four robust setae in the middle. Labial palp with segment I 0.8× the length of segments II and III combined; inner projection of labial palp of segment II rounded, outer margin and projection covered with thin, long, simple setae; segment III triangular, covered with thin, long, simple setae on outer margin, dorsal surface with one row of six robust setae, outer margin almost straight. Thorax. Foreleg (
<figureCitation id="3B9E2A26FF969E630FD1F8A69E450074" box="[1192,1281,1879,1905]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[176,1408,182,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-30@6.[176,1411,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3A–J. Apobaetis jacobusi sp. nov. A. labrum (left d.v., right v.v.); B. left mandible; C. right mandible; D. maxilla; E. hypopharynx; F. labium (left d.v., right v.v.); G. foreleg; H. posterior margin of tergum IV; I. gill VI; J. paraproct." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4296592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4296592/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="254">Fig. 3G</figureCitation>
). Femur: with one row of eight short blunt setae on dorsal margin; apex with two short blunt setae; ventral margin with one row of six short robust setae. Tibia: ventrally with one row of 12 short robust setae. Patella-tibial suture from dorsal to ventral margin. Tarsus: ventrally with one row of 12 short robust setae. Tarsal claws the same length as tarsus, row of denticles absent. Claws II and III slightly longer than tarsus. Abdomen. Tergum II darker, tergum V with one dark mark, terga V–IX with one reddish mark on distolateral margin (
<figureCitation id="3B9E2A26FF9B9E6E0809FF4A98FC07D0" box="[880,952,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[207,1380,189,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-19@7.[207,1380,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4A–D. Larval habitus. A. Apobaetis biancae sp. nov., dorsal view; B. Apobaetis biancae sp. nov., lateral view; C. Apobaetis jacobusi sp. nov., dorsal view; D. Apobaetis jacobusi sp. nov., lateral view; E. Apobaetis jacobusi sp. nov., ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4296594" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4296594/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="257">Figs 4</figureCitation>
C–4E). Tergal surface creased, with micropores (not illustrated); posterior margin with triangular spines (longer than wide) (
<figureCitation id="3B9E2A26FF9B9E6E0F4CFF2E9FD407FC" box="[1077,1168,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[176,1408,182,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-30@6.[176,1411,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3A–J. Apobaetis jacobusi sp. nov. A. labrum (left d.v., right v.v.); B. left mandible; C. right mandible; D. maxilla; E. hypopharynx; F. labium (left d.v., right v.v.); G. foreleg; H. posterior margin of tergum IV; I. gill VI; J. paraproct." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4296592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4296592/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="257">Fig. 3H</figureCitation>
). Gill VI, rounded (
<figureCitation id="3B9E2A26FF9B9E6E0E16FF2E9BF40618" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[176,1408,182,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-30@6.[176,1411,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3A–J. Apobaetis jacobusi sp. nov. A. labrum (left d.v., right v.v.); B. left mandible; C. right mandible; D. maxilla; E. hypopharynx; F. labium (left d.v., right v.v.); G. foreleg; H. posterior margin of tergum IV; I. gill VI; J. paraproct." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4296592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4296592/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="257">Fig. 3I</figureCitation>
), outer margin slightly expanded (all other gills broken and lost). Paraproct (
<figureCitation id="3B9E2A26FF9B9E6E0F6CFEF29F200618" box="[1045,1124,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[176,1408,182,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-30@6.[176,1411,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3A–J. Apobaetis jacobusi sp. nov. A. labrum (left d.v., right v.v.); B. left mandible; C. right mandible; D. maxilla; E. hypopharynx; F. labium (left d.v., right v.v.); G. foreleg; H. posterior margin of tergum IV; I. gill VI; J. paraproct." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4296592" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4296592/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="257">Fig. 3J</figureCitation>
) with four marginal spines, posterolateral extension with few spines. Cerci and paracercus with lateral spines on all segments.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
